1
00:00:01,636 --> 00:00:05,598
At Sonoko's invitation, we visited the set of a TV show—

2
00:00:05,681 --> 00:00:09,018
me, Ran, Sera, and Uncle Kogoro.

3
00:00:09,769 --> 00:00:15,191
But when the recording began and we opened the locked box containing fruit—

4
00:00:15,274 --> 00:00:18,319
which would determine the fate of the pastry chefs' victory or defeat—

5
00:00:18,653 --> 00:00:21,322
inside was the body of the head judge,

6
00:00:21,405 --> 00:00:23,991
Mr. Shoutoku Takegi.

7
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:25,910
What doesn't sit right with us

8
00:00:25,993 --> 00:00:28,579
is Takegi-san's behavior.

9
00:00:29,080 --> 00:00:32,833
Why was he so obsessively checking the box?

10
00:00:33,876 --> 00:00:36,003
Don't you think he thought he'd been found out?

11
00:00:36,587 --> 00:00:39,340
The champion who's been winning for six consecutive weeks—

12
00:00:39,423 --> 00:00:41,384
Kurimura-san. Huh?

13
00:00:41,801 --> 00:00:45,346
That champion always brought ingredients

14
00:00:45,429 --> 00:00:47,807
that matched the theme fruit,

15
00:00:47,890 --> 00:00:51,102
so maybe he knew what was inside the box.

16
00:00:51,185 --> 00:00:53,479
Chief Megure! Hmm?

17
00:00:54,230 --> 00:00:55,439
It seems Takegi-san—

18
00:00:55,523 --> 00:00:58,067
last night, mixed in with the extras for a period drama,

19
00:00:58,150 --> 00:01:00,236
sneaked into the TV station.

20
00:01:00,653 --> 00:01:01,946
I see.

21
00:01:02,029 --> 00:01:04,740
He wanted to make it seem like he wasn't at the TV station

22
00:01:04,824 --> 00:01:07,952
to make it easier for the culprit to show their hand.

23
00:01:08,035 --> 00:01:12,331
Takegi-san was hiding in the warehouse where that box was stored,

24
00:01:12,415 --> 00:01:15,209
so it's highly likely he was lying in wait for the culprit.

25
00:01:18,212 --> 00:01:22,299
On the seams of the box's lid and inside it,

26
00:01:22,717 --> 00:01:25,469
there were traces of blood that had been wiped away.

27
00:01:25,803 --> 00:01:29,390
That means the place where the box was kept is the crime scene, right?

28
00:01:32,727 --> 00:01:36,230
Takegi-san was murdered there.

29
00:01:39,358 --> 00:01:41,652
By the culprit who secretly opened the box.

30
00:01:45,865 --> 00:01:47,408
By the culprit.

31
00:01:48,534 --> 00:01:54,540
♪~♪

32
00:02:01,756 --> 00:02:05,259
The blackness of shadows, the density of darkness—
the light of reasoning cuts right through them.

33
00:02:05,342 --> 00:02:09,096
What is the trick hidden in the box,
and what is the key to the evidence pointing to the culprit?

34
00:02:09,180 --> 00:02:10,431
See through the one and only truth.

35
00:02:10,514 --> 00:02:12,641
Looks like a kid, but has the mind of an adult.

36
00:02:12,725 --> 00:02:15,061
His name is Detective Conan!

37
00:03:39,911 --> 00:03:45,917
♪~♪

38
00:03:47,111 --> 00:03:52,811
"A Treasure Box Full of Fruits (Part 2)"

39
00:03:56,427 --> 00:03:58,304
Ah, here he comes. Oh...

40
00:03:58,930 --> 00:04:01,098
Isn't this Takegi-san?

41
00:04:01,390 --> 00:04:04,894
See, while looking around, into the warehouse...

42
00:04:05,811 --> 00:04:09,106
The question is, who will come next?

43
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:12,610
Like I said, it's probably him.

44
00:04:12,693 --> 00:04:15,112
No, it's... Hmm?

45
00:04:16,447 --> 00:04:18,449
Producer Taruoka?

46
00:04:18,699 --> 00:04:20,910
Wh... why you?

47
00:04:20,993 --> 00:04:24,121
Well... as the producer,

48
00:04:24,205 --> 00:04:27,124
I came to check that the box was delivered properly.

49
00:04:27,792 --> 00:04:29,377
Takegi-san also warned me,

50
00:04:29,460 --> 00:04:31,087
"If the contents were leaked,

51
00:04:31,170 --> 00:04:32,588
it would be your responsibility."

52
00:04:32,672 --> 00:04:34,715
He had firmly warned me.

53
00:04:35,132 --> 00:04:36,217
Hmm?

54
00:04:36,550 --> 00:04:40,596
Still, you were in there a long time—
about 30 minutes.

55
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:43,516
No, no, I forgot where the box was placed,

56
00:04:43,599 --> 00:04:45,351
so I was searching for it.

57
00:04:45,434 --> 00:04:47,895
The warehouse is big and cluttered.

58
00:04:47,979 --> 00:04:50,731
Hmm? Next is... Ah.

59
00:04:51,232 --> 00:04:56,153
Assistant Director Furuya, and he's brought two young ADs.

60
00:04:58,948 --> 00:05:01,492
You were inside quite a long time too.

61
00:05:01,575 --> 00:05:02,743
Ah. Hmm?

62
00:05:02,827 --> 00:05:06,288
Actually, I finished checking the box quickly

63
00:05:06,372 --> 00:05:07,873
and was smoking.

64
00:05:08,457 --> 00:05:10,668
The station is mostly non-smoking,

65
00:05:10,751 --> 00:05:14,046
and ADs are so busy they don't have time to smoke.

66
00:05:14,380 --> 00:05:17,466
I was checking my email for 3 to 4 minutes.

67
00:05:17,550 --> 00:05:20,219
Well, the warehouse is non-smoking too, though.

68
00:05:21,721 --> 00:05:24,056
Oh, he's out.

69
00:05:24,140 --> 00:05:27,226
You were inside for about 30 minutes too, huh?

70
00:05:28,853 --> 00:05:31,355
If no one went in after this,

71
00:05:31,439 --> 00:05:33,899
then the suspects are you two...

72
00:05:33,983 --> 00:05:36,152
Eh? Ah, actually—

73
00:05:36,235 --> 00:05:38,237
I also went into the warehouse.

74
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:40,740
Eh? Kasuga-san too?

75
00:05:40,823 --> 00:05:43,367
Yes. I was worried about something Takegi-san told me,

76
00:05:43,451 --> 00:05:44,785
so—

77
00:05:44,869 --> 00:05:45,953
I was confident in the lock I had put on,

78
00:05:46,037 --> 00:05:47,538
but I hadn't checked the TV station's lock properly.

79
00:05:47,621 --> 00:05:49,457
I hadn't checked it.

80
00:05:49,540 --> 00:05:51,333
I hadn't checked it.

81
00:05:51,417 --> 00:05:53,419
Ah, that's right.

82
00:05:53,669 --> 00:05:55,629
Kasuga-san, you came too.

83
00:05:56,005 --> 00:06:00,760
I think I was inside for about 30 minutes,
just like the previous two.

84
00:06:01,260 --> 00:06:04,263
After all, I carefully and thoroughly examined it,

85
00:06:04,346 --> 00:06:08,976
and took several photos to show Takegi-san later.

86
00:06:09,060 --> 00:06:11,187
And what were the results?

87
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:13,314
The lock was completely secured,

88
00:06:13,397 --> 00:06:16,067
so I went home after that.

89
00:06:16,150 --> 00:06:19,320
Hmm... after Kasuga-san left,

90
00:06:19,403 --> 00:06:22,573
until several staff members took the box the next day,

91
00:06:22,656 --> 00:06:25,409
it seems no one else entered the warehouse.

92
00:06:25,993 --> 00:06:27,328
In other words—

93
00:06:27,661 --> 00:06:31,916
Among the three—Producer Taruoka,
AD Furuya-san,

94
00:06:31,999 --> 00:06:36,420
and food coordinator Kasuga-san—

95
00:06:36,504 --> 00:06:40,257
is the culprit who murdered Takegi-san.

96
00:06:46,889 --> 00:06:51,227
So, the suspects have been narrowed down to three,

97
00:06:51,310 --> 00:06:54,105
but who is the culprit?

98
00:06:54,188 --> 00:06:58,609
More importantly, the method used to open the lock is a mystery.

99
00:06:59,235 --> 00:07:01,612
Unless we figure that out—

100
00:07:01,695 --> 00:07:02,780
Hmm?

101
00:07:03,697 --> 00:07:06,200
But still, why are there so many packed in there?

102
00:07:06,283 --> 00:07:08,702
Even if you combine the champion and challenger,

103
00:07:08,786 --> 00:07:11,789
they wouldn't use 10 of them during the show.

104
00:07:11,872 --> 00:07:13,624
You don't even understand that?

105
00:07:13,707 --> 00:07:14,750
Huh?

106
00:07:16,043 --> 00:07:19,463
A box full of fruit looks better on screen.

107
00:07:20,214 --> 00:07:21,507
The leftover fruit

108
00:07:21,590 --> 00:07:25,177
is given away to the audience by lottery after each recording.

109
00:07:25,594 --> 00:07:28,013
Well, they use a false bottom so the box isn't too heavy.

110
00:07:28,097 --> 00:07:30,641
Well, they use a false bottom so the box isn't too heavy.

111
00:07:30,724 --> 00:07:35,146
And because they're rare fruits that are hard to get,

112
00:07:35,229 --> 00:07:38,566
there are apparently a lot of people who apply to the audience
just for that.

113
00:07:38,649 --> 00:07:40,401
there are apparently a lot of people who apply to the audience
just for that.

114
00:07:40,651 --> 00:07:41,944
Hmm.

115
00:07:42,027 --> 00:07:43,320
So? Have you figured out who the culprit is?

116
00:07:43,404 --> 00:07:44,822
So? Have you figured out who the culprit is?

117
00:07:44,905 --> 00:07:47,032
Not at all.

118
00:07:47,491 --> 00:07:50,369
I don't even have a clue about how the lock was opened.

119
00:07:50,452 --> 00:07:54,790
Well, that's trivial compared to that mystery.

120
00:07:54,874 --> 00:07:56,917
That mystery? Huh?

121
00:07:57,334 --> 00:07:59,003
What is it?

122
00:07:59,086 --> 00:08:02,590
Hey, hey, you really haven't noticed?

123
00:08:02,673 --> 00:08:04,717
Yeah. Guh...

124
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:08,888
How could you not notice something this important?

125
00:08:08,971 --> 00:08:11,223
Listen carefully.

126
00:08:11,849 --> 00:08:14,393
It's about Yoko-chan's hair in the back.

127
00:08:14,476 --> 00:08:18,022
In the last live show, it was quite short,

128
00:08:18,105 --> 00:08:20,024
but today it's long.

129
00:08:20,316 --> 00:08:23,068
That growth rate isn't normal.

130
00:08:23,444 --> 00:08:25,863
Ah, that's probably extensions.

131
00:08:25,946 --> 00:08:28,616
Huh? Exten...

132
00:08:28,699 --> 00:08:32,369
Short for hair extensions. Fake hair.

133
00:08:33,245 --> 00:08:34,413
Fake hair?

134
00:08:34,663 --> 00:08:36,457
In Yoko-chan's case,

135
00:08:36,540 --> 00:08:40,336
she probably hid them well at the hair clip.

136
00:08:40,419 --> 00:08:41,879
Is that so?

137
00:08:41,962 --> 00:08:43,088
Ah.

138
00:08:43,839 --> 00:08:46,425
I see. So that's it.

139
00:08:46,884 --> 00:08:49,803
If that's the case, then the culprit can only be that person...

140
00:08:50,638 --> 00:08:54,934
Ah, you just thought the same thing as me, didn't you?

141
00:08:55,017 --> 00:08:57,937
Huh? Hmm? Hmm?

142
00:09:00,147 --> 00:09:03,150
These buck teeth that show up when she smiles...

143
00:09:07,655 --> 00:09:10,824
But the problem is the evidence.

144
00:09:11,575 --> 00:09:13,077
I knew it. I've—

145
00:09:13,786 --> 00:09:16,038
met this girl somewhere before...

146
00:09:17,164 --> 00:09:18,374
Hmm?

147
00:09:18,791 --> 00:09:20,334
What? What is it?

148
00:09:20,417 --> 00:09:23,212
Is there something on my face?

149
00:09:23,295 --> 00:09:25,798
Ah, no. It's nothing.

150
00:09:28,217 --> 00:09:29,885
We've taken photos,

151
00:09:29,969 --> 00:09:32,388
so shall we take the box back and examine it thoroughly?

152
00:09:32,471 --> 00:09:33,597
Yeah.

153
00:09:34,431 --> 00:09:35,516
Hey. Huh?

154
00:09:35,599 --> 00:09:38,477
Are those all the apples that were in the box?

155
00:09:38,727 --> 00:09:40,479
Ah... yeah.

156
00:09:40,562 --> 00:09:42,648
I think there were a lot of apples that spilled out of the box

157
00:09:42,731 --> 00:09:46,652
and got squeezed inside the lid.

158
00:09:47,069 --> 00:09:49,113
We put them all inside.

159
00:09:49,196 --> 00:09:52,700
They probably just spilled out when the box was opened.

160
00:09:53,367 --> 00:09:56,537
Hey, you always said that box was packed full of the theme fruit, right?

161
00:09:56,620 --> 00:09:58,747
Hey, you always said that box was packed full of the theme fruit, right?

162
00:09:58,831 --> 00:10:02,584
Yeah, so packed that 2 or 3 apples would spill out.

163
00:10:02,668 --> 00:10:05,671
Because the host Kenzaki-san's catchphrase is,

164
00:10:06,171 --> 00:10:07,214
"Look at this!"

165
00:10:07,298 --> 00:10:10,968
"These overflowing fruits!"

166
00:10:11,927 --> 00:10:13,595
If that's the case...

167
00:10:14,763 --> 00:10:16,640
That becomes evidence.

168
00:10:19,268 --> 00:10:20,311
Ah, hey!

169
00:10:20,769 --> 00:10:22,396
That little brat.

170
00:10:22,479 --> 00:10:25,858
It's just like when he's with Hattori-kun.

171
00:10:25,941 --> 00:10:28,485
Hmm? What's wrong, Ran?

172
00:10:28,569 --> 00:10:30,154
Wave... Huh?

173
00:10:30,237 --> 00:10:34,783
Whenever I see Sera-san running away,

174
00:10:35,075 --> 00:10:37,411
I always hear it in the back of my ear.

175
00:10:37,911 --> 00:10:42,708
(Sound of waves)

176
00:10:49,006 --> 00:10:50,966
The sound of ripples...

177
00:10:51,467 --> 00:10:53,886
as if by magic.

178
00:10:55,679 --> 00:10:58,265
Ran? Ah... oh!

179
00:10:58,349 --> 00:11:02,770
What? Don't tell me you've fallen for that kid.

180
00:11:02,853 --> 00:11:04,938
It's nothing like that.

181
00:11:05,022 --> 00:11:08,192
Hmph. It's just because that boastful kid is a returnee.

182
00:11:08,275 --> 00:11:09,943
That's why I feel that way.

183
00:11:10,027 --> 00:11:12,613
Huh? How does that make sense?

184
00:11:12,988 --> 00:11:16,950
See, because she came from overseas, "outside the sea."

185
00:11:17,242 --> 00:11:19,036
That's why.

186
00:11:19,119 --> 00:11:20,496
Uh...

187
00:11:20,579 --> 00:11:22,331
A dad joke.

188
00:11:22,581 --> 00:11:24,458
Why won't you let me in?

189
00:11:24,666 --> 00:11:26,960
Just for a little bit, okay?

190
00:11:27,044 --> 00:11:31,090
No way. This warehouse is where the box was kept,

191
00:11:31,173 --> 00:11:33,467
and it's also the murder scene.

192
00:11:33,842 --> 00:11:37,012
Then, did you find anything inside the warehouse?

193
00:11:37,096 --> 00:11:41,183
So far, nothing related to the case...

194
00:11:41,475 --> 00:11:44,144
Then, did anything unusual happen inside?

195
00:11:44,228 --> 00:11:47,731
Ah, come to think of it, when we went in to investigate,

196
00:11:47,815 --> 00:11:50,484
a young AD was getting scolded

197
00:11:50,567 --> 00:11:53,362
because the props used for the drama's kitchen set

198
00:11:53,445 --> 00:11:55,489
hadn't been washed properly.

199
00:11:55,864 --> 00:11:57,366
The kitchen's...

200
00:11:57,616 --> 00:11:59,076
props.

201
00:11:59,493 --> 00:12:02,621
Well, it probably has nothing to do with the case.

202
00:12:02,704 --> 00:12:04,289
Hey. Hmm?

203
00:12:04,665 --> 00:12:07,668
Those three suspects are still here, right?

204
00:12:07,751 --> 00:12:11,255
Yeah, they're waiting in another room.

205
00:12:11,338 --> 00:12:14,675
All three are asking to be released soon.

206
00:12:14,758 --> 00:12:15,801
Ah...

207
00:12:15,884 --> 00:12:19,221
The producer, Taruoka-san, said

208
00:12:19,304 --> 00:12:22,433
there's a press conference about the case...

209
00:12:22,516 --> 00:12:25,727
AD Furuya-san said he hasn't eaten anything since morning,

210
00:12:25,811 --> 00:12:28,188
so please let him go eat.

211
00:12:28,439 --> 00:12:30,691
The food coordinator, Kasuga-san, said

212
00:12:30,774 --> 00:12:34,820
he wants to go home to feed his pet dog.

213
00:12:35,571 --> 00:12:38,198
Then we should start quickly.

214
00:12:38,574 --> 00:12:40,659
Eh? Start what?

215
00:12:40,951 --> 00:12:43,412
What? A little...

216
00:12:43,954 --> 00:12:45,873
magic show.

217
00:12:56,076 --> 00:12:58,245
Hah? A magic show?

218
00:12:58,704 --> 00:13:02,958
Did you call us and the suspects here just to see something like that?

219
00:13:03,042 --> 00:13:05,461
And the one performing is that boastful kid?

220
00:13:05,544 --> 00:13:06,754
Now, now.

221
00:13:07,129 --> 00:13:09,965
I think if you see it, you'll be surprised.

222
00:13:10,049 --> 00:13:11,091
Hmm...

223
00:13:11,550 --> 00:13:14,595
Hey, Conan-kun isn't here.

224
00:13:14,678 --> 00:13:17,473
Isn't he with Sera-san?

225
00:13:17,931 --> 00:13:19,475
Here he is.

226
00:13:22,352 --> 00:13:23,562
Whoa!

227
00:13:23,645 --> 00:13:27,066
Welcome to Sera Masumi's House of Magic!

228
00:13:27,149 --> 00:13:29,693
Ah... Wait, don't tell me...

229
00:13:30,319 --> 00:13:34,198
The box you're sitting in... is that the one the victim was put in?

230
00:13:34,281 --> 00:13:35,783
Well, yeah.

231
00:13:36,492 --> 00:13:39,161
And I also have this box's padlock

232
00:13:39,244 --> 00:13:41,622
and the key to open it.

233
00:13:41,705 --> 00:13:43,082
Hey, hey.

234
00:13:43,165 --> 00:13:47,336
We asked the prop master to prepare a similar box.

235
00:13:47,419 --> 00:13:49,713
The key is real, though.

236
00:13:49,797 --> 00:13:52,591
So? What's about to start?

237
00:13:52,883 --> 00:13:55,552
First of all...

238
00:13:56,845 --> 00:14:00,265
please make sure there's nothing inside the box.

239
00:14:00,641 --> 00:14:01,975
Hmm. Hmph.

240
00:14:02,935 --> 00:14:05,229
Hmm... Hmm...

241
00:14:07,523 --> 00:14:09,108
It seems empty.

242
00:14:09,191 --> 00:14:10,901
Eh... yes.

243
00:14:10,984 --> 00:14:13,320
Okay, now...

244
00:14:16,907 --> 00:14:21,120
Close the lid, pass the iron bar of the padlock

245
00:14:21,411 --> 00:14:24,414
through the holes at the seams of the box,

246
00:14:25,999 --> 00:14:28,669
and click it locked.

247
00:14:31,213 --> 00:14:34,508
See? Without the padlock key,

248
00:14:34,591 --> 00:14:36,510
the box shouldn't open, right?

249
00:14:36,844 --> 00:14:38,178
Huh? Yeah.

250
00:14:38,262 --> 00:14:41,849
So take this key and go outside the room for a bit.

251
00:14:41,932 --> 00:14:44,059
Huh? We have to go out?

252
00:14:44,143 --> 00:14:47,479
Heh heh. After Takagi-keiji finishes talking,

253
00:14:47,563 --> 00:14:49,022
you can come back in.

254
00:14:49,106 --> 00:14:50,232
Ta... Takagi's?

255
00:14:50,315 --> 00:14:52,526
Ah, hey... hey, Conan-kun...

256
00:14:54,903 --> 00:14:57,364
Hmm? Oh, that's right.

257
00:14:57,447 --> 00:14:58,949
(Clears throat)

258
00:14:59,533 --> 00:15:01,535
Now, let me explain.

259
00:15:01,910 --> 00:15:04,621
The key to this case is—

260
00:15:04,705 --> 00:15:06,790
the locked box.

261
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:09,293
Food coordinator Kasuga-san

262
00:15:09,376 --> 00:15:12,671
packed the box with fruit, locked it with a padlock,

263
00:15:12,754 --> 00:15:14,756
and sent it to the TV station.

264
00:15:14,840 --> 00:15:17,718
Producer Taruoka, who received it,

265
00:15:17,801 --> 00:15:22,055
instructed AD Furuya-san to put another padlock on it

266
00:15:22,139 --> 00:15:25,893
and send it back to Kasuga-san.

267
00:15:25,976 --> 00:15:30,272
Then Kasuga-san removed his own padlock,

268
00:15:30,355 --> 00:15:32,691
sent it back to the TV station again,

269
00:15:32,774 --> 00:15:36,820
and it was stored in the warehouse until the recording began.

270
00:15:36,904 --> 00:15:41,116
Why was Takegi-san's body inside that box?

271
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:43,076
That's the question.

272
00:15:43,493 --> 00:15:47,748
Of course, when Kasuga-san first locked the box,

273
00:15:47,831 --> 00:15:51,627
AD Furuya-san, who came from the TV station to pick up the box,

274
00:15:51,710 --> 00:15:53,837
AD Furuya-san, who came from the TV station to pick up the box,

275
00:15:53,921 --> 00:15:57,591
confirmed that Takegi-san was not inside.

276
00:15:58,342 --> 00:16:02,721
Furthermore, the key is a special key with no duplicates,

277
00:16:02,804 --> 00:16:06,016
so it's not easy to force it open.

278
00:16:06,099 --> 00:16:09,770
And of course, there's no hidden door on the box.
Given this situation—

279
00:16:09,853 --> 00:16:12,731
How did the culprit... Hmm...

280
00:16:12,814 --> 00:16:15,859
Enough with the preamble! Just tell us the answer!

281
00:16:15,943 --> 00:16:18,946
Tell us, Takagi-keiji!

282
00:16:19,029 --> 00:16:21,073
Huh? Dahahaha!

283
00:16:21,156 --> 00:16:25,202
It's faster to show you than to explain.

284
00:16:26,787 --> 00:16:30,207
The answer is exactly this.

285
00:16:31,041 --> 00:16:32,501
Ah!

286
00:16:33,252 --> 00:16:35,337
Co... Conan-kun!

287
00:16:35,420 --> 00:16:37,381
Wh... where were you?

288
00:16:37,464 --> 00:16:39,967
I was hiding behind the box.

289
00:16:41,218 --> 00:16:43,512
More importantly, where's Sera-san?

290
00:16:43,845 --> 00:16:47,015
Hehehehe. Where do you think?

291
00:16:47,099 --> 00:16:50,394
Hey, don't tell me... Inside the box?

292
00:16:52,813 --> 00:16:56,275
Don't be stupid. It's properly locked, isn't it?

293
00:16:56,358 --> 00:16:58,402
Then why don't you open it?

294
00:17:07,452 --> 00:17:10,205
Ta-da! Huh? Uh...

295
00:17:10,289 --> 00:17:12,207
Huh? Heh heh.

296
00:17:15,210 --> 00:17:16,378
No way.

297
00:17:16,461 --> 00:17:17,796
Why?

298
00:17:19,673 --> 00:17:21,341
I used this.

299
00:17:21,425 --> 00:17:22,592
Hmm?

300
00:17:23,552 --> 00:17:25,470
A rubber tube?

301
00:17:25,554 --> 00:17:29,182
It's painted gold to match the padlock.

302
00:17:29,808 --> 00:17:33,103
I had the prop master make it.

303
00:17:33,186 --> 00:17:35,314
But how did you use it?

304
00:17:35,605 --> 00:17:36,690
Yeah, yeah.

305
00:17:37,190 --> 00:17:40,068
Then I'll show you using this.

306
00:17:40,485 --> 00:17:42,112
Lend me that padlock too.

307
00:17:42,195 --> 00:17:43,655
Ah... yeah.

308
00:17:44,656 --> 00:17:47,242
When putting on the padlock,

309
00:17:47,326 --> 00:17:50,078
fit the tube onto the tip of the bar,

310
00:17:50,871 --> 00:17:55,208
and forcefully jam it into the padlock's hole.

311
00:17:55,834 --> 00:17:57,711
See? If you do it like this,

312
00:17:57,794 --> 00:18:00,339
it looks like it's locked, right?

313
00:18:00,422 --> 00:18:02,841
Wow! You're right.

314
00:18:02,924 --> 00:18:04,593
Ah...

315
00:18:04,676 --> 00:18:06,386
I... indeed.

316
00:18:06,470 --> 00:18:08,638
With this, you can easily remove the padlock

317
00:18:08,722 --> 00:18:11,391
just by twisting the lock...

318
00:18:11,475 --> 00:18:14,561
And moreover, the seam where the tube is attached

319
00:18:14,644 --> 00:18:16,480
is hidden by the part of the box's seam

320
00:18:16,563 --> 00:18:20,734
that the padlock bar goes through, so you can't see it.

321
00:18:20,984 --> 00:18:24,946
That means I pretended to lock it with that tube,

322
00:18:25,030 --> 00:18:27,908
then removed the padlock, got into the box,

323
00:18:27,991 --> 00:18:31,828
and Conan-kun, who was hiding behind the box, pulled out the tube,

324
00:18:31,912 --> 00:18:35,123
and then locked it properly with the padlock.

325
00:18:35,207 --> 00:18:37,334
Hmm. Right.

326
00:18:37,417 --> 00:18:40,295
The key point of this trick is the padlock—

327
00:18:41,588 --> 00:18:44,341
the fact that it can be locked without the key.

328
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:48,303
Kasuga-san, who knew the contents of the box from the beginning,

329
00:18:48,387 --> 00:18:52,349
would have no need to go to the trouble of rigging it to open the lid...

330
00:18:52,891 --> 00:18:57,562
And Producer Taruoka, who instructed that the padlock be put on,

331
00:18:57,771 --> 00:19:00,482
had no opportunity to use this trick.

332
00:19:01,650 --> 00:19:03,777
Which leaves—

333
00:19:03,860 --> 00:19:07,739
AD Wataru Furuya, who was instructed by Taruoka
to put on the lock and send it back.

334
00:19:09,116 --> 00:19:11,118
AD Wataru Furuya.

335
00:19:11,201 --> 00:19:12,619
Ah...

336
00:19:14,621 --> 00:19:16,957
I think it can only be you.

337
00:19:17,040 --> 00:19:18,875
Ah. Huh?

338
00:19:21,086 --> 00:19:22,629
I'm sure you were opening the box in the warehouse

339
00:19:22,712 --> 00:19:26,591
to tell the champion the theme fruit inside, in exchange for a reward.

340
00:19:27,008 --> 00:19:30,429
to tell the champion the theme fruit inside, in exchange for a reward.

341
00:19:33,265 --> 00:19:34,808
(Sound) Ah.

342
00:19:36,226 --> 00:19:38,937
Last night, Takegi-san was hiding there,

343
00:19:40,522 --> 00:19:44,234
and when he caught you, you got into a struggle...

344
00:19:45,569 --> 00:19:46,736
Ah!

345
00:19:46,820 --> 00:19:49,197
Ugh... ngh...

346
00:19:50,365 --> 00:19:52,492
You killed him by accident,

347
00:19:52,826 --> 00:19:56,496
and in a panic, you hid him inside the box, right?

348
00:19:56,955 --> 00:19:59,458
Wh... where is the evidence for that?

349
00:19:59,541 --> 00:20:01,334
There is evidence. Huh?

350
00:20:01,710 --> 00:20:03,879
It's inside your stomach, AD-san.

351
00:20:03,962 --> 00:20:06,173
Huh? AD-san.

352
00:20:06,256 --> 00:20:08,800
After you put that old man in the box,

353
00:20:08,884 --> 00:20:12,304
you blended up about 10 apples that wouldn't fit and drank them, right?

354
00:20:12,387 --> 00:20:15,932
You put them in the mixer prop that was in the warehouse.

355
00:20:16,433 --> 00:20:19,102
The AD caught on the security camera

356
00:20:19,186 --> 00:20:22,689
wasn't carrying anything when he came out of the warehouse.

357
00:20:24,232 --> 00:20:28,069
E... even if that's true, they've already been digested in my stomach...

358
00:20:28,153 --> 00:20:29,654
You didn't know? Huh?

359
00:20:31,156 --> 00:20:32,574
Apple seeds contain

360
00:20:32,657 --> 00:20:35,535
components that are poisonous.

361
00:20:35,619 --> 00:20:37,370
Eating a lot of them is dangerous.

362
00:20:37,454 --> 00:20:38,455
Huh...

363
00:20:38,872 --> 00:20:41,791
AD-san, when you put the apples in the mixer,

364
00:20:41,875 --> 00:20:44,419
you didn't take out the seeds, did you?

365
00:20:44,503 --> 00:20:45,837
Ugh...

366
00:20:46,421 --> 00:20:48,465
Well, it's okay.

367
00:20:48,548 --> 00:20:53,136
With only the seeds from about 10 apples, it won't be dangerous.

368
00:20:53,220 --> 00:20:54,679
Ugh...

369
00:20:54,763 --> 00:20:59,559
But since you haven't eaten anything since morning,
the "big one" should still be there.

370
00:20:59,643 --> 00:21:01,811
It'll come out eventually, won't it?

371
00:21:02,103 --> 00:21:05,774
The rare apple seeds that the mixer failed to crush.

372
00:21:05,857 --> 00:21:08,068
Ugh... ugh...

373
00:21:09,027 --> 00:21:10,153
Heh heh.

374
00:21:11,071 --> 00:21:14,574
Once that comes out, Case Closed.

375
00:21:14,658 --> 00:21:18,203
Talk about running out of luck.

376
00:21:19,454 --> 00:21:25,460
♪~♪

377
00:22:33,278 --> 00:22:39,034
~♪

378
00:22:39,117 --> 00:22:42,954
Oh, it's on the online news!

379
00:22:43,038 --> 00:22:44,623
Just like Sera-san said,

380
00:22:44,706 --> 00:22:48,877
seeds came out of the AD and matched the theme apples.

381
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:52,589
It seems the champion, Kurimura-san, also confessed.

382
00:22:52,672 --> 00:22:55,967
That he had asked about the theme fruit in advance.

383
00:22:56,509 --> 00:22:59,471
But Conan-kun surprises me again.

384
00:22:59,554 --> 00:23:03,808
I didn't know apple seeds are toxic.

385
00:23:03,892 --> 00:23:07,937
I just happened to remember hearing it from Shinichi-niichan.

386
00:23:08,521 --> 00:23:11,733
You and Shinichi-kun are really close.

387
00:23:11,816 --> 00:23:15,111
Ah, th... that reminds me. Hmm?

388
00:23:16,738 --> 00:23:19,991
There's something I want to ask Sera-neechan.

389
00:23:20,075 --> 00:23:22,619
Ah, you did say that.

390
00:23:22,952 --> 00:23:25,830
Sera-neechan... don't tell me...

391
00:23:27,332 --> 00:23:29,876
Have we met somewhere before?

392
00:23:34,130 --> 00:23:35,131
Huh?

393
00:23:38,218 --> 00:23:40,804
Who knows? Huh?

394
00:23:41,513 --> 00:23:44,974
Sorry, but I can't tell you that.

395
00:23:45,975 --> 00:23:48,478
Until the time comes.

396
00:23:51,898 --> 00:23:54,567
These are things my late husband collected.

397
00:23:54,651 --> 00:23:55,735
I see.

398
00:23:57,612 --> 00:23:58,947
Ah... whoa!

399
00:23:59,030 --> 00:24:02,033
Hey, Dad, be careful.

400
00:24:02,117 --> 00:24:03,201
I know!

401
00:24:03,618 --> 00:24:04,994
What is the meaning of this?

402
00:24:05,078 --> 00:24:06,579
What's all this noise?

403
00:24:06,830 --> 00:24:09,833
Why did you cancel my passing of the audition?

404
00:24:12,836 --> 00:24:15,505
The lady's room is... Mama.

405
00:24:16,172 --> 00:24:19,882
Next Conan...
"The Diamond, the Painting, and the Great Actress"

406
00:24:37,196 --> 00:24:39,657
Next Conan's Hint:
"Sunlight"

407
00:24:41,409 --> 00:24:43,536
Speaking of light, it's time for this star, Kogoro, to appear.

408
00:24:43,620 --> 00:24:44,662
You're pretty energetic today.

409
00:24:44,746 --> 00:24:46,372
Because I'm not doing any deducing.
